==Notes== <!--T:20-->

<!--T:21-->
* {{PropertyData|helix_angle}} ({{Emphasis|beta}}, <math>\beta</math>): Changing the helix angle does not change the pitch pitch, or more precise the transverse pitch (<math>p_t</math>) since the {{PropertyData|module}} property represents the transverse module (<math>m_t</math>) unless the {{PropertyData|properties_from_tool}} property is {{true}}. In that case it represents the normal module (<math>m_n</math>), that has to be divided by <math> cos (\beta)</math> and thus enlarged to give the transverse module (<math>m_t</math>) needed to calculate the {{PropertyData|transverse_pitch}} property (<math>p_t</math>).
** Spur rack: <math>\beta = 0^\circ</math>,  <math>\cos (\beta) = 1 </math> and <math>m_t = m_n</math>
** Helical rack: <math>\beta > 0^\circ</math>,  <math>\cos (\beta) < 1 </math> and <math>m_t =  \frac{m_n}{\cos (\beta)}</math>
** <math>p_t = m_t \cdot \pi =  \frac {m_n} {\cos (\beta)} \cdot \pi</math>
*  {{PropertyData|transverse_pitch}} (<math>p_t</math>): The transverse pitch is the transverse module  (<math>m_t</math>) multiplied by pi: <math>p_t = m_t \cdot \pi</math>
** The transverse pitch multiplied by the number of teeth (<math>z</math>) gives the length (<math>l</math>) of the rack: <math>l = p_t \cdot z</math>
* {{PropertyData|clearance}} (<math>c</math>): At a gear pair, clearance is the distance between the tooth tip of the first gear and the tooth root of the second gear.
* {{PropertyData|double_helix}}: Activates double helical gearing if the {{PropertyData|helix_angle}} property is larger than 0 (<math>\beta > 0^\circ</math>).

<!--T:47-->
* {{PropertyData|module}} (<math>m</math>): Using ISO (International Organization for Standardization) guidelines, Module size is designated as the unit representing gear tooth-sizes.
** The module multiplied by Pi (<math>\pi</math>) defines the pitch (<math>p</math>), the distance between corresponding points of adjacent teeth: <math>p = m \cdot \pi</math>
* {{PropertyData|pressure_angle}} (<math>\alpha</math>): Only change the parameter, if sufficient knowledge of the gear geometry is available.

